        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks JL for his book [<hi rend="italic">Origin of civilization</hi> (1870)], which he has read with "extreme interest". Wishes JL had published four or five months earlier as CD would have "so profited &amp; saved so much work". CD will have to modify some of what he has written [in <hi rend="italic">Descent</hi>]. Sees they differ a good deal about moral sense "but hardly two men ever do agree on this perplexing subject".</p>  
<p>JL’s note of the 16th [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">7277</hi>] about the Census arrived too late for CD to answer.</p> 
        </abstract>
